<tt>Mon Sep 13  7:17:07 US/Eastern 1999
</tt><p>
My father once told me that he did not know if PTSD was something that  he would ever claim to have but he did not look negatively upon those who did. He expected nothing and was proud to have served and do his duty. My father would never give me the answers I asked for when I asked about his life in vietnam. I realize now that I was young and could never understand that war the way he experienced it. I love and respect my dad for being a good father but I wish I could have been able to share more. He died 3 yrs ago and my family tells me stories and I read his letters home. I dont know how you vets did it. You all amaze me. I appreciate your forums and words....they make me feel closer to dad....I wish he knew how much I look up to him and respect him. I hope you all allow your children to try to understand the life you lived. Going through my early 20's I realized I could never fathom  his life. I am so proud he was my dad.
<p><code>-- Andrewlucs@webtv.net  (Andy Lucas) </code><p>


